<subSubSection box="[199,1220,225,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,395]" box="[199,1220,225,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,225,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Etymology:</emphasis>
This species named based on the joined (connected) apical bands on the wing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="428" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,261,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Coquillett)" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[675,943,261,288]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Acrotaeniostola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinaria">
<emphasis box="[675,803,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">A. quinaria</emphasis>
(Coquillett)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1014,1084,261,287]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1095,1197,261,287]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1210,1267,261,287]" name="Laos" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Laos</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1279,1377,261,287]" name="Vietnam" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Malaysia" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and Sumatra in general appearance, but can be differentiated by the fused apical and subapical wing bands, which are separate in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[398,529,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Acrotaeniostola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinaria">
A. 
<emphasis box="[433,529,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">quinaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; constriction of aculeus tip before prepical setae, which is broad in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1300,1428,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Acrotaeniostola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinaria">
<emphasis box="[1300,1317,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1332,1428,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">quinaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and deeper concavity of sternite V in males, which is shallow/flat in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[919,1046,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Acrotaeniostola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinaria">
<emphasis box="[919,936,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[950,1046,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="428">quinaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
